Date: 1996-10-01

Title: Gauge invariance and mass gap in (2+1)-dimensional Yang-Mills theory

Authors: Dimitra Karabali and V.P. Nair

Comments: 10 pages, Plain TeX, talk presented at the Workshop on Low

Dimensional Field Theories, Telluride, August 1996Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A12 (1997) 1161-1172

In terms of a gauge-invariant matrix parametrization of the fields, we givean analysis of how the mass gap could arise in non-Abelian gauge theories intwo spatial dimensions.